WEBVTT

00:02.040 --> 00:03.710
Katie: No, no, no!

00:03.710 --> 00:04.830
I did not spend an entire day
doing laundry

00:04.830 --> 00:06.290
just to have it ruined
by one stupid sock!

00:06.290 --> 00:08.170
Tell me
where your friend is!

00:08.170 --> 00:10.210
Answer me,
you son of a bitch!

00:10.210 --> 00:11.250
Don't worry --

00:11.250 --> 00:13.080
she always swears
at the laundry.

00:13.080 --> 00:15.120
Now, what causes thunder?

00:15.120 --> 00:16.500
Oh, I know this one!

00:16.500 --> 00:18.580
Thunder happens
when two clouds

00:18.580 --> 00:20.710
bump into each other
super hard.

00:20.710 --> 00:23.830
[ Pen scratching ]
Super...hard.

00:23.830 --> 00:25.120
Greg: Actually, Trip,

00:25.120 --> 00:26.540
thunder occurs
when lightning,

00:26.540 --> 00:28.250
which is a discharge
of electricity,

00:28.250 --> 00:30.000
shoots through the air,
causing vibrations.

00:30.000 --> 00:31.580
[ Scoffs ]
Good one, Mr. A.

00:31.580 --> 00:33.330
"Vibrations."

00:33.330 --> 00:35.170
[ Both laugh ]

00:35.170 --> 00:36.380
Hey, Dad, after we're
finished studying,

00:36.380 --> 00:37.790
can Trip and I
go see a midnight movie?

00:37.790 --> 00:39.960
Sounds fun, but you have to ask
your Mom first.

00:41.420 --> 00:43.040
You know that
she can't be out till 2:00 a.m.

00:43.040 --> 00:44.250
on a school night.

00:44.250 --> 00:46.420
Why do you always make me
the bad cop?

00:46.420 --> 00:47.960
'Cause you're so good
at it.
Yeah.

00:47.960 --> 00:49.540
Spoiling fun.

00:49.540 --> 00:51.120
That's what attracted me
to the parenting business

00:51.120 --> 00:52.710
to begin with.

00:52.710 --> 00:56.380
Taylor, absolutely
no midnight movies.

00:56.380 --> 00:57.790
Trip: Don't worry, babe.

00:57.790 --> 00:59.420
We'll just see
a midnight movie earlier,

00:59.420 --> 01:00.420
at like 9:00.

01:00.420 --> 01:02.670
You are so smart.

01:02.670 --> 01:04.380
[ Giggles ]

01:04.380 --> 01:05.620
[ Laughs ]

01:05.620 --> 01:06.790
[ Laughs ]

01:06.790 --> 01:08.210
Uh, hey, guys.

01:08.210 --> 01:10.210
Hey, Dad.
Mr. A!

01:10.210 --> 01:11.290
-[ Laughs ]
-Oh, I almost forgot.

01:11.290 --> 01:12.710
How am I supposed
to do the laundry

01:12.710 --> 01:13.830
without the laundry?

01:13.830 --> 01:16.120
[ Footsteps ]

01:18.420 --> 01:20.830
[ Laughing ] Mm.

01:22.210 --> 01:24.670
Katie, can you come here
for a minute?

01:24.670 --> 01:27.000
[ Sighs ] What's up?

01:27.000 --> 01:28.210
Nothing.

01:32.540 --> 01:36.040
[ Laughs ]

01:36.040 --> 01:37.120
[ Laughing ]

01:38.790 --> 01:39.670
Katie!

01:39.670 --> 01:41.210
Katie: Ohh.

01:41.210 --> 01:42.580
What do you want, Greg?

01:42.580 --> 01:44.670
I want you to stay in this room
and never leave, ever.

01:44.670 --> 01:45.880
Does that mean
I stay here

01:45.880 --> 01:47.080
and you do
the grocery shopping?

01:47.080 --> 01:48.420
Is this some sort of trick

01:48.420 --> 01:49.790
to get almond butter
back in the house?

01:49.790 --> 01:50.750
Not falling for it.

01:53.750 --> 01:55.460
Want a back rub?
Yay!

01:56.750 --> 01:57.750
Mm.

01:57.750 --> 01:59.250
Wow.

01:59.250 --> 02:01.580
Your corneas
are so tight.
Mm.

02:01.580 --> 02:05.210
♪♪

02:05.210 --> 02:07.170
Oliver,
here's your laundry.

02:07.170 --> 02:09.120
I put anything you labeled
"dry clean only"

02:09.120 --> 02:10.500
in the washer

02:10.500 --> 02:13.210
because dry cleaning
is just a bunch of voodoo.

02:14.620 --> 02:16.580
Why are you taking down
all your stuff?

02:16.580 --> 02:18.420
Did the ghost of
Westport Douche Future

02:18.420 --> 02:19.580
pay you a visit?

02:19.580 --> 02:21.420
Gina is coming over
for the first time,

02:21.420 --> 02:23.420
and I don't want her to get
the wrong impression.

02:23.420 --> 02:24.500
If she sees all this,
she might think I'm a...

02:24.500 --> 02:26.710
Materialistic snob?
A preppy idiot?

02:26.710 --> 02:28.500
A pubescent Mr. Monopoly?

02:28.500 --> 02:30.500
Oliver, I'm landing shots
left and right here.

02:30.500 --> 02:31.580
Stand up for yourself.

02:31.580 --> 02:32.710
Mom, this is serious.

02:32.710 --> 02:34.080
Gina isn't from Westport.

02:34.080 --> 02:35.250
She's from South Brampton,

02:35.250 --> 02:37.380
so she's not
into the whole money thing.

02:37.380 --> 02:39.250
So you're telling me

02:39.250 --> 02:41.790
that you are willing to change
your entire personality

02:41.790 --> 02:42.670
for your new girlfriend?

02:42.670 --> 02:44.210
You're disappointed.

02:44.210 --> 02:45.750
You think I should be myself,
no matter what?

02:45.750 --> 02:46.880
Of course not.

02:46.880 --> 02:48.620
I love
that you're changing!

02:48.620 --> 02:50.120
Your personality
is terrible.

02:50.120 --> 02:52.380
Ladies and gentlemen,
my mom.

02:52.380 --> 02:55.790
No, I mean,
it is terrible.

02:55.790 --> 02:57.040
If I wasn't your mother,
I'd be like,

02:57.040 --> 02:58.080
"Who is your mother?"

02:58.080 --> 03:00.330
♪♪

03:04.670 --> 03:06.380
Neeeigh!

03:06.380 --> 03:09.710
Ahhhhhh-
uuuuuuuuuuuuuuuunck!

03:09.710 --> 03:11.670
I made a T. rex noise.

03:11.670 --> 03:13.080
Be better, Franklin.

03:14.380 --> 03:15.790
Anna-Kat, you're never gonna
believe what just happened.

03:15.790 --> 03:17.040
Try me.

03:17.040 --> 03:18.330
You know how
I've been trying

03:18.330 --> 03:19.620
to teach your brother
that money isn't everything?

03:19.620 --> 03:21.790
Well, I think he finally
learned his lesson,

03:21.790 --> 03:23.460
thanks to
that new girlfriend of his.

03:23.460 --> 03:26.330
A lot of windup
for very little payoff.

03:26.330 --> 03:28.040
I can see
you're not the audience

03:28.040 --> 03:30.000
for news about
Oliver's personal growth.
Nope.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.540
Now, if you'll excuse us,

03:31.540 --> 03:33.000
I have to teach Franklin

03:33.000 --> 03:34.710
how to make pony noises
correctly.

03:34.710 --> 03:36.790
Mm.

03:36.790 --> 03:38.080
Can I go home yet?

03:38.080 --> 03:40.460
This playdate is over
when I say it's over.

03:40.460 --> 03:43.080
Hey, great news --

03:43.080 --> 03:45.540
Oliver is becoming
less of a materialistic jerk

03:45.540 --> 03:47.040
because of
Gina Tuscadero.

03:47.040 --> 03:48.710
Yeah, well,
I have terrible news.

03:48.710 --> 03:50.290
I just got
a back rub from Trip,

03:50.290 --> 03:51.380
and it felt amazing.

03:51.380 --> 03:53.120
Why did you let him
give you a back rub?

03:53.120 --> 03:54.710
It was the only thing
I could do

03:54.710 --> 03:56.210
to keep his hands
off Taylor.

03:56.210 --> 03:57.670
Those two
are all over each other.

03:57.670 --> 03:58.750
I didn't see anything.

03:58.750 --> 04:00.170
That's because,
for some strange reason,

04:00.170 --> 04:01.540
they're never handsy
in front of you.

04:01.540 --> 04:02.750
Oh...

04:02.750 --> 04:05.210
That's because no one fears
the good cop.

04:05.210 --> 04:06.540
You give them dessert
before dinner.

04:06.540 --> 04:08.170
You do their homework
when they fall behind.

04:08.170 --> 04:11.250
Taylor knows not to pull
that PDA stuff around me.

04:11.250 --> 04:13.920
But with the good cop,
anything goes.

04:13.920 --> 04:15.580
I want to learn to be
a less likable parent.

04:15.580 --> 04:17.250
Teach me.

04:17.250 --> 04:19.710
Next time you see
Taylor and Trip's PDA,

04:19.710 --> 04:21.500
shut it down
with "The Look."

04:21.500 --> 04:22.330
What's "The Look"?

04:23.830 --> 04:24.920
Ooh, that's good.

04:24.920 --> 04:26.420
Shuts the kids down
every time.

04:26.420 --> 04:27.210
Give it a try.

04:29.080 --> 04:30.250
You holding in a fart,
Greg?

04:30.250 --> 04:31.420
No,
I'm trying to look mean.

04:31.420 --> 04:32.250
Well, try harder.

04:32.250 --> 04:33.580
Remember how angry you were

04:33.580 --> 04:35.960
when we walked into
that Abe Lincoln-themed diner

04:35.960 --> 04:38.040
and they sat us in
the John Wilkes Booth booth?

04:40.040 --> 04:41.460
There it is.

04:41.460 --> 04:42.460
[ Doorbell rings ]

04:42.460 --> 04:43.920
That must be Gina.

04:45.380 --> 04:47.290
The girl who made our son
less of a tool

04:47.290 --> 04:48.500
and, through
her parents' restaurant,

04:48.500 --> 04:50.830
has unlimited access
to pizza.

04:50.830 --> 04:52.210
Pinch me!
I think I'm dreaming.
Greg: [ Chuckles ]

04:53.420 --> 04:56.290
Remember,
Gina is a regular girl.

04:56.290 --> 04:58.500
This is no time to stop
acting like yourselves.

04:58.500 --> 05:00.080
[ Door opens ]

05:00.080 --> 05:01.790
Hey, Gina.
Hey, Oliver.

05:01.790 --> 05:04.920
[ Chuckling ] Wow.
Your house is so nice.

05:04.920 --> 05:06.330
Thanks.

05:06.330 --> 05:08.460
Just two good,
hardworking people,

05:08.460 --> 05:10.750
trying their best to provide
for their family.

05:10.750 --> 05:11.790
I'll sign the papers

05:11.790 --> 05:13.210
for their teen marriage
right now.

05:13.210 --> 05:15.830
You remember
my mom and dad.

05:15.830 --> 05:18.120
And my sister Taylor
and her boyfriend, Trip.

05:18.120 --> 05:20.170
And this is
my little sister Anna-Kat

05:20.170 --> 05:21.710
and her friend Franklin.

05:21.710 --> 05:26.500
[ Dramatic music plays ]

05:26.500 --> 05:29.040
Actually, Franklin and I
just made it official.

05:29.040 --> 05:30.420
We're an item now.

05:30.420 --> 05:31.620
What's an item?

05:31.620 --> 05:33.500
How I hooked this tuna,
I'll never know.

05:33.500 --> 05:34.290
[ Chuckles ]

05:37.000 --> 05:38.120
Come on in.
[ Chuckles ]

05:40.380 --> 05:42.670
So, Gina...

05:44.000 --> 05:45.290
Oh, come on.

05:45.290 --> 05:46.830
These dishes are so nice.

05:46.830 --> 05:49.210
Thank you.
I got them from CVS.

05:49.210 --> 05:52.380
And this shirt's from Ross,
from the irregular bin.

05:52.380 --> 05:54.000
Well, you better not
tell anybody,

05:54.000 --> 05:55.580
or they'll kick you
out of Westport.

05:55.580 --> 05:57.580
[ Laughter ]

05:57.580 --> 06:00.080
Look at that --
Oliver fell for his mother.

06:00.080 --> 06:02.210
Yeah,
Westport's the worst.

06:02.210 --> 06:03.790
All people care about is
showing off how rich they are.

06:03.790 --> 06:05.040
[ Door opens ]

06:05.040 --> 06:06.790
Buenos días, Ottos!

06:06.790 --> 06:09.540
Check out what I just charged
to my black Amex.

06:09.540 --> 06:11.960
It is a custom-made,
Italian leather tote bag.

06:11.960 --> 06:14.080
Everyone,
form a line to feel.

06:14.080 --> 06:16.040
Who is this?

06:16.040 --> 06:17.830
I'm Cooper,
Oliver's best friend.

06:17.830 --> 06:19.710
[ Scoffs ] Really?

06:19.710 --> 06:21.830
Cooper and I
hang out on occasion.

06:21.830 --> 06:22.830
All the time.

06:22.830 --> 06:24.210
Now, dude, let's go.

06:24.210 --> 06:25.540
There's a bocce tournament
at the club,

06:25.540 --> 06:27.750
and I have to swing by the house
to change into my whites.

06:29.080 --> 06:30.620
This is eggshell.

06:30.620 --> 06:31.830
Oh.

06:31.830 --> 06:33.920
Actually, Gina and I
are going mini-golfing.

06:33.920 --> 06:36.330
Not enough Purell
in the world, brotha.

06:36.330 --> 06:38.290
Has anyone ever described you
as "punchable"?

06:39.750 --> 06:41.250
Sorry, Coop.

06:41.250 --> 06:42.540
Gina and I
already made plans.

06:42.540 --> 06:44.380
You and I can go to the club
another time.

06:44.380 --> 06:45.670
Come on, Oliver,

06:45.670 --> 06:47.500
we gotta leave now
if we want to catch the bus.

06:47.500 --> 06:48.830
Don't worry about it.
I'll give you a ride.

06:48.830 --> 06:50.750
Did you not hear me?

06:50.750 --> 06:52.210
It's Bocce Day.

06:52.210 --> 06:53.920
Bocce!

06:56.790 --> 06:58.250
[ Door closes ]

06:58.250 --> 06:59.880
That girl's trouble,
Mrs. Otto.

06:59.880 --> 07:01.330
She's not like one of us.

07:01.330 --> 07:02.790
Cooper: [ Sighs ]

07:02.790 --> 07:04.710
You don't have
any Fiji Water.

07:04.710 --> 07:07.000
I'll put that
on your shopping list.

07:07.000 --> 07:08.040
Cooper, the only reason
you're in this house

07:08.040 --> 07:09.210
is Oliver's here.

07:09.210 --> 07:11.170
So when he's not here,

07:11.170 --> 07:12.460
you're not here.

07:12.460 --> 07:13.290
¿Comprende?

07:14.500 --> 07:22.120
♪♪

07:22.120 --> 07:24.420
Smart --
age up the leather.

07:26.460 --> 07:28.120
I don't want to look like
new money.

07:30.420 --> 07:32.540
Oliver is becoming
a better person,

07:32.540 --> 07:34.000
and I might finally have

07:34.000 --> 07:35.710
his obnoxious
Richie Rich friend

07:35.710 --> 07:37.540
out of my life forever.

07:37.540 --> 07:40.250
The only way
this day could get better

07:40.250 --> 07:42.330
is if I found that --

07:42.330 --> 07:43.960
Move over,
birth of my children.

07:43.960 --> 07:46.040
This is officially
the best day of my life.

07:46.040 --> 07:47.210
Vacation's over, bitch.

07:47.210 --> 07:47.920
♪♪

07:52.170 --> 07:53.580
[ Thunder crashing ]

07:53.580 --> 07:55.540
Narrator: When lightning shoots
through the air,

07:55.540 --> 07:57.330
it causes vibrations
that we call "thunder."

07:57.330 --> 07:58.710
Now do you believe me?

07:58.710 --> 08:00.000
[ Chuckles ]

08:00.000 --> 08:01.830
Way to double down
on a joke, Mr. A.

08:01.830 --> 08:04.880
So, Anna-Kat, how long have
you and Franklin been dating?

08:04.880 --> 08:06.250
You mean,
when did we first know

08:06.250 --> 08:07.750
we were madly in love?
Mm-hmm.

08:07.750 --> 08:09.420
That's
a great question.

08:09.420 --> 08:11.420
Sweetie,
when did we first know?

08:11.420 --> 08:13.000
I have an extra toe.

08:13.000 --> 08:14.500
[ Laughing ] Oh, Franklin.

08:14.500 --> 08:16.000
The things you say.

08:16.000 --> 08:18.250
Narrator:
This is a cumulus cloud.

08:18.250 --> 08:20.830
And this is
an altocumulus cloud.

08:20.830 --> 08:22.120
And this is...

08:22.120 --> 08:23.620
Katie: A bored housewife
closing her eyes.

08:23.620 --> 08:24.670
See ya.

08:28.250 --> 08:29.580
[ Both laugh ]

08:29.580 --> 08:30.580
[ Clears throat ]
Taylor.

08:33.000 --> 08:34.830
Whoa!
Dad, are you okay?

08:34.830 --> 08:36.330
Is your IBS acting up?

08:36.330 --> 08:38.380
I'm fine.
Just focus on the program.

08:41.250 --> 08:42.380
[ Both laugh ]

08:42.380 --> 08:43.330
[ Clears throat ]

08:47.670 --> 08:49.710
Mr. A, I definitely think
something is wrong.

08:49.710 --> 08:51.670
My dog made the same face
you're making now,

08:51.670 --> 08:53.170
and later that day,
he died.

08:53.170 --> 08:54.880
We need to get you to a vet,
ASAP.

08:54.880 --> 08:56.580
Trip, the only thing
that's wrong with me

08:56.580 --> 08:57.710
is the fact that you two

08:57.710 --> 08:59.170
won't keep your hands
off each other!

09:00.420 --> 09:02.460
Dad, you're being so uncool
right now.

09:02.460 --> 09:03.880
I don't care.

09:03.880 --> 09:06.420
Taylor, your PDA
is completely unacceptable,

09:06.420 --> 09:08.000
and I will not have it
in this house anymore.

09:08.000 --> 09:09.040
Are we clear?

09:09.620 --> 09:10.670
Of course, sir.

09:12.210 --> 09:13.710
I should go.

09:14.710 --> 09:16.000
[ Sighs softly ]

09:16.500 --> 09:18.170
Trip and I like each other.

09:18.170 --> 09:19.920
We're just doing
what couples do.

09:19.920 --> 09:21.170
I expect mom to freak out,

09:21.170 --> 09:22.540
but I thought
you were cooler than that.

09:23.880 --> 09:25.620
I guess I was wrong.

09:25.620 --> 09:27.210
Move over, Bruce Willis.

09:27.210 --> 09:29.250
There's a new bad cop
on the force.

09:29.250 --> 09:31.420
Yippee-daba-doo,
mother-may-I.

09:32.710 --> 09:33.670
Is that right?

09:33.670 --> 09:35.080
No.

09:35.080 --> 09:37.540
♪♪

09:37.540 --> 09:39.000
Grand?

09:39.000 --> 09:41.500
More like a bland jeté,
Rachel.
Rachel's garbage.

09:41.500 --> 09:42.540
Cooper: Hey, amigo.

09:42.540 --> 09:44.290
Dónde está you been?

09:44.290 --> 09:45.960
I gave you a call
yesterday.
Yeah.

09:45.960 --> 09:47.580
Conveniently,
when you knew I'd be

09:47.580 --> 09:49.330
at my grass court
tennis lesson.

09:49.330 --> 09:50.750
Why'd he say what the court
was made out of?

09:50.750 --> 09:52.420
It's one of those
Westport things.

09:52.420 --> 09:54.420
Hey, Oliver,
you live in Westport.

09:54.420 --> 09:55.670
Dude, what's your deal?

09:55.670 --> 09:56.960
You meet her,

09:56.960 --> 09:58.250
and suddenly you're acting
all not high and mighty.

09:58.250 --> 10:00.210
Cooper,
let's talk about this later.
No.

10:00.210 --> 10:01.500
I want
to talk about it now.

10:01.500 --> 10:02.670
If she doesn't want
to hang out with me, I --

10:02.670 --> 10:04.670
She never said that.
I didn't say it yet.

10:04.670 --> 10:06.460
See? She said it.

10:06.460 --> 10:08.120
She still hasn't
technically said it.

10:08.120 --> 10:10.380
I don't want
to hang out with you.

10:11.670 --> 10:13.380
Well, now she said it.

10:13.380 --> 10:14.620
Looks like you're gonna
have to choose.

10:15.920 --> 10:18.080
Is it me or her?

10:18.080 --> 10:19.120
Don't be like that.

10:19.120 --> 10:20.330
Oliver, let's go.

10:20.330 --> 10:22.670
It's high noon,
muchacho.

10:22.670 --> 10:28.210
♪♪

10:28.210 --> 10:29.670
I'll see you around,
Cooper.

10:30.750 --> 10:32.460
You get a girlfriend
and blow off your buddy --

10:32.460 --> 10:34.040
fine.

10:34.040 --> 10:35.710
Just remember,
before I took you under my wing,

10:35.710 --> 10:37.710
you were nothing!

10:37.710 --> 10:40.580
You wore seersucker in the Fall
like a friggin' townie!

10:40.580 --> 10:44.000
♪♪

10:44.000 --> 10:46.210
It's so cool
that you have a pig as a pet.

10:46.210 --> 10:48.580
Oh, yeah, I love him.
[ Snorting ]

10:48.580 --> 10:51.000
Can't get enough
of this filthy guy.

10:51.000 --> 10:52.210
[ Laughs ]

10:54.880 --> 10:55.960
Hey, Mom.
Katie: Mm-hmm.

10:55.960 --> 10:57.620
I need some advice.
Sure.

10:57.620 --> 10:59.080
Stop wearing
your sister's jeans.

10:59.080 --> 11:00.500
Boom! Up top!

11:01.120 --> 11:02.120
Don't be mad.

11:02.120 --> 11:03.460
You give me a setup
like that,

11:03.460 --> 11:04.620
I'm gonna crush it.

11:04.620 --> 11:06.380
Cooper and Gina
don't get along,

11:06.380 --> 11:08.170
and they made me
choose sides.
Mm-hmm.

11:08.170 --> 11:09.170
I picked Gina,

11:09.170 --> 11:10.790
and now Cooper and I
aren't talking.

11:10.790 --> 11:12.250
What should I do?
Nothing.

11:12.250 --> 11:14.040
It's always
hos before bros.

11:14.040 --> 11:16.000
Isn't it
bros before hos?

11:16.000 --> 11:17.500
Hey, this is 2018.

11:17.500 --> 11:20.000
There has been real progress
in this country.

11:20.000 --> 11:21.710
Hos have come a long way.

11:21.710 --> 11:22.960
You guys ready to go?

11:22.960 --> 11:24.620
I'm dropping them off
at Gina's family's restaurant.

11:24.620 --> 11:26.120
The kids
will have dinner there.

11:26.120 --> 11:28.000
Mm.
Dad, you should come in
and grab a calzone.

11:28.000 --> 11:30.250
Wow. Normally, you ask me
to come to a rolling stop,

11:30.250 --> 11:31.920
and then you say,
"Thanks, Uber driver."

11:31.920 --> 11:33.290
[ Chuckles ]
He's joking.

11:33.960 --> 11:35.880
Hey, Franklin, why don't
you come with us, buddy?

11:35.880 --> 11:37.250
Your house is on the way.

11:37.250 --> 11:39.250
You're leaving
without saying goodbye?

11:39.250 --> 11:42.420
Seriously, Franklin,
what is happening to us?

11:42.420 --> 11:44.040
I wanted
to name my cat Mittens,

11:44.040 --> 11:45.710
but my mom
wouldn't let me.

11:45.710 --> 11:46.960
Now its name is Phillip.

11:46.960 --> 11:48.210
Wow.
[ Door opens ]

11:48.210 --> 11:50.290
I think we should take
some time to cool off

11:50.290 --> 11:52.080
before we say something
we regret.

11:52.080 --> 11:53.960
[ Sighs ]

11:53.960 --> 11:55.210
I'll be in my room,

11:55.210 --> 11:57.290
listening to the sad song
from "Mulan."

11:59.790 --> 12:01.250
[ Snorting ]

12:01.250 --> 12:02.670
Looks like it's just
you and me for dinner,

12:02.670 --> 12:03.790
Hans Gruber.

12:03.790 --> 12:05.460
[ Door opens ]

12:05.460 --> 12:07.120
Hola, Mrs. Otto.

12:07.120 --> 12:08.330
Adiós, Cooper.
[ Door closes ]

12:08.330 --> 12:09.540
Oliver's not here.

12:09.540 --> 12:11.250
Oh, I know.
I just saw him leave.

12:11.250 --> 12:12.620
I actually came here
to see you.

12:12.620 --> 12:14.000
Me?
Yeah.

12:14.000 --> 12:16.080
It's bad enough
I lose my best friend,

12:16.080 --> 12:17.580
but that means
I also lose you.

12:20.000 --> 12:21.080
Me?

12:21.080 --> 12:22.380
Yeah.

12:22.380 --> 12:24.080
I mean, my parents
travel all the time,

12:24.080 --> 12:25.290
so you're, like,
the only one

12:25.290 --> 12:27.040
who's looking out
for good ole Cooper B.

12:27.040 --> 12:29.040
But all I do
is yell at you.

12:29.040 --> 12:30.380
Yeah, we have
a good back-and-forth.

12:30.380 --> 12:34.120
So, anyway,
I just came by to say...

12:34.120 --> 12:38.000
I'm gonna, you know,
miss you.

12:38.000 --> 12:39.710
And stuff.

12:39.710 --> 12:46.670
[ Slow music plays ]

12:46.670 --> 12:47.500
[ Breathes sharply ]

12:47.500 --> 12:48.920
Cooper.

12:48.920 --> 12:50.250
Yeah?

12:50.250 --> 12:51.380
Have you eaten yet?

12:51.380 --> 12:52.920
No.

12:52.920 --> 12:54.460
Then, why don't you sit down
and have dinner with me?

12:54.460 --> 12:56.460
Really?!
Mm-hmm.

12:56.460 --> 12:58.040
[ Chuckling ]
Thanks, Mrs. Otto.

12:58.040 --> 13:00.380
Just so you know,
I'm not expecting
anything fancy.

13:00.380 --> 13:01.540
I'll be fine with
whatever you're making.

13:01.540 --> 13:03.880
I'll just put
some truffle oil on it.

13:03.880 --> 13:05.170
I don't have truffle oil.

13:05.170 --> 13:06.710
Oh, shaved truffles
are fine.

13:06.710 --> 13:07.880
If you say "truffles" again,

13:07.880 --> 13:09.080
I will beat you
with this broom handle.

13:09.080 --> 13:10.960
See,
this is the back-and-forth

13:10.960 --> 13:11.960
that I'm talking about.

13:11.960 --> 13:13.750
Mm-hmm. [ Chuckles ]

13:13.750 --> 13:17.790
♪♪

13:17.790 --> 13:19.880
I had the chance to get
that spoiled, arrogant brat

13:19.880 --> 13:21.120
out of my life
once and for all.

13:21.120 --> 13:22.330
Oliver's gone?!

13:22.330 --> 13:23.380
I'm talking about Cooper.

13:23.380 --> 13:24.420
Pay attention, Doris.

13:24.420 --> 13:25.790
I let him stay for dinner,

13:25.790 --> 13:27.080
and by
the end of the night,

13:27.080 --> 13:28.170
I am blow-torching
his pudding

13:28.170 --> 13:29.670
to make it a crème brûlée.

13:29.670 --> 13:31.670
[ Chuckles ] It sounds like
he needs you in his life.

13:31.670 --> 13:33.420
I know,
and I want to help him,

13:33.420 --> 13:35.210
but I can't have Gina
going anywhere.

13:35.210 --> 13:37.790
She's made Oliver
mildly pleasant.

13:37.790 --> 13:39.210
Then you're gonna have
to teach Cooper

13:39.210 --> 13:40.540
to be less
of a spoiled brat.

13:40.540 --> 13:41.920
I just got Anna-Kat
to learn

13:41.920 --> 13:43.170
flushing is not optional.

13:43.170 --> 13:45.000
I don't have time
for extracurricular mothering.

13:45.000 --> 13:47.460
At least I have the Taylor
situation under control.

13:47.460 --> 13:49.830
She and her boyfriend
have been a little too PDA-y,

13:49.830 --> 13:52.170
and I told Greg that he needs
to put his foot down,

13:52.170 --> 13:53.380
and he actually did.

13:53.380 --> 13:55.710
Oh. So they're not
all over each other anymore?

13:55.710 --> 13:56.670
Haven't even seen them.

13:59.920 --> 14:02.040
Dude,
you played that all wrong.

14:02.040 --> 14:03.330
So wrong.

14:03.330 --> 14:05.080
Why?

14:05.080 --> 14:06.620
You want Taylor and Trip
to make out at your house

14:06.620 --> 14:08.170
'cause then they'd be
at your house.
Mm-hmm.

14:08.170 --> 14:09.790
They could be anywhere
right now,

14:09.790 --> 14:11.380
doing anything.

14:11.380 --> 14:13.540
God, you're right.

14:13.540 --> 14:15.330
I was the girl
who didn't bring boyfriends home

14:15.330 --> 14:16.790
because I didn't
like my parents.
Mm-hmm.

14:16.790 --> 14:19.170
And what were you and
your boyfriend doing
at Taylor's age?

14:19.170 --> 14:22.710
Well, they called me
"Everything Goes Katie," so...

14:22.710 --> 14:24.040
[ Gasps ] Oh, God!

14:24.040 --> 14:27.500
♪♪

14:27.500 --> 14:30.290
You see, Cooper has no one
looking out for him,

14:30.290 --> 14:31.920
so with him,
by being the bad cop,

14:31.920 --> 14:33.580
I'm actually
the good cop.

14:33.580 --> 14:34.580
And with Taylor,

14:34.580 --> 14:36.210
me being the bad cop
wasn't a good thing.

14:36.210 --> 14:38.000
Yeah, because now she's off
somewhere with Trip,

14:38.000 --> 14:39.290
playing
the childhood favorite,

14:39.290 --> 14:40.380
"You show me yours,
I'll show you mine."

14:40.380 --> 14:42.420
Aah! That's my baby!

14:42.420 --> 14:44.380
Come on, Greg.
She's 16.

14:44.380 --> 14:45.830
Don't make me
go to the la-la-la's.

14:45.830 --> 14:48.000
Face it --
your baby has urges.

14:48.000 --> 14:49.750
La-la-la-la, la-la-la-la,

14:49.750 --> 14:51.330
la-la-la-la, la-la-la-la!
Fine. I'll stop.

14:51.330 --> 14:52.170
La-la.

14:52.170 --> 14:53.790
I've got to work
with Cooper,

14:53.790 --> 14:55.250
and you've got to make it

14:55.250 --> 14:57.250
so that Taylor and Trip
feel comfortable in the house

14:57.250 --> 14:58.460
so that we can
keep an eye on her.

14:58.460 --> 15:00.710
So I want Taylor and Trip
to make out in front of me,

15:00.710 --> 15:02.790
and you want to spend more time
with Cooper Bradford?

15:02.790 --> 15:04.250
I know I say this a lot,

15:04.250 --> 15:06.210
so it's lost a little bit
of its meaning,

15:06.210 --> 15:07.920
but the kids
have truly ruined our lives.

15:07.920 --> 15:10.170
♪♪

15:14.330 --> 15:15.750
So, to stay friends
with Oliver,

15:15.750 --> 15:17.120
you have to become friends
with Gina.

15:17.120 --> 15:18.120
Is that it?

15:18.120 --> 15:19.250
[ Scoffs ] So easy.

15:19.250 --> 15:20.210
For a girl like Gina,

15:20.210 --> 15:21.750
I bet her number's
pretty low.

15:21.750 --> 15:22.670
5 grand feels right.

15:22.670 --> 15:24.290
You can't buy
her friendship.

15:24.290 --> 15:25.960
You are going to
have to stop acting

15:25.960 --> 15:27.960
like an entitled ass,

15:27.960 --> 15:30.120
and I'm going to
teach you how.

15:30.120 --> 15:31.670
Lesson one --

15:31.670 --> 15:34.380
never say "custom-made
Italian leather tote bag"

15:34.380 --> 15:36.120
ever again.

15:36.120 --> 15:37.290
Lesson one,

15:37.290 --> 15:39.580
and I'm already way outside
my comfort zone.

15:39.580 --> 15:41.420
[ Sighs ]

15:41.420 --> 15:43.420
See, all of these things
in here

15:43.420 --> 15:45.330
are meals that normal people
would eat.

15:45.330 --> 15:47.750
Chicken fingers?
That's a meal.

15:47.750 --> 15:49.210
Those look gross,

15:49.210 --> 15:51.000
but with
a little truffle oil --

15:55.080 --> 15:56.620
Say you're at a restaurant,

15:56.620 --> 15:59.330
and you accidentally
knock over someone's drink.

15:59.330 --> 16:00.670
What do you do?

16:00.670 --> 16:02.790
I crumple two $50s
and throw it at them.

16:02.790 --> 16:04.250
No.

16:04.250 --> 16:06.120
You say "sorry"
and offer to clean it up.

16:06.120 --> 16:07.750
How do you know
all this stuff?

16:07.750 --> 16:09.880
[ Sighs ]

16:09.880 --> 16:12.040
♪♪

16:12.040 --> 16:13.420
Anna-Kat: Dr. Ellie,

16:13.420 --> 16:16.290
in the beginning,
Franklin was so romantic.

16:16.290 --> 16:18.420
He picked me first
at dodgeball,

16:18.420 --> 16:20.460
he gave me
all the good crayons,

16:20.460 --> 16:22.040
but now,

16:22.040 --> 16:24.580
it's like we're not even
in the same conversation.

16:24.580 --> 16:26.290
Anna-Kat,
I don't think Franklin

16:26.290 --> 16:28.000
is acting like
he's in a relationship.

16:28.000 --> 16:30.420
You hit the nail
on the head, Doc.

16:30.420 --> 16:31.460
No, I mean,

16:31.460 --> 16:33.120
you're in a relationship
with Franklin,

16:33.120 --> 16:34.500
but he's not in one
with you.

16:34.500 --> 16:35.830
Franklin doesn't even know

16:35.830 --> 16:36.960
you guys
are boyfriend-girlfriend.

16:36.960 --> 16:38.920
Is that true, Franklin?

16:38.920 --> 16:40.290
What class is this?

16:40.290 --> 16:41.790
You see what
I'm dealing with here?

16:41.790 --> 16:44.170
I'm going to my mother's.

16:44.170 --> 16:49.330
♪♪

16:49.330 --> 16:50.670
Taylor! Can I talk to you
for a minute?!

16:50.670 --> 16:51.790
Taylor: What?!

16:51.790 --> 16:52.880
[ Footsteps ]

16:55.540 --> 16:57.540
I just wanted to tell you
I made a mistake.

16:57.540 --> 16:59.170
Your and Trip's PDA
is normal,

16:59.170 --> 17:00.960
and I was wrong
to get in the way of that.

17:00.960 --> 17:02.960
I accept your apology.

17:02.960 --> 17:06.000
And no more intercepting
my back rubs.
Fine.

17:06.000 --> 17:07.580
Because you're comfortable

17:07.580 --> 17:08.790
showing how you feel about Trip
in front of me,

17:08.790 --> 17:10.580
I'm comfortable showing
how I feel about your mother

17:10.580 --> 17:11.710
in front of you.

17:11.710 --> 17:13.880
Kitty Cat, are you there?

17:13.880 --> 17:16.500
Yes, Snuggle Bug?

17:16.500 --> 17:18.670
I just wanted to tell you
I love you very, very much.

17:18.670 --> 17:20.380
Katie:
That is so sweet.

17:20.380 --> 17:22.670
Seems like Papa Bear
deserves a widdle kiss.

17:22.670 --> 17:24.000
Aww.

17:25.920 --> 17:27.830
Taylor:
All right, I get it. Okay.

17:27.830 --> 17:29.420
[ Chuckling ] Okay.

17:29.420 --> 17:31.120
Okay! Stop!

17:31.920 --> 17:33.330
Oh, we're just showing
that we like each other.

17:33.330 --> 17:34.210
That's
what couples do.
Mm-hmm.

17:35.540 --> 17:36.830
All right.

17:36.830 --> 17:38.170
Okay. I get it.

17:38.170 --> 17:39.380
I get it!

17:39.380 --> 17:41.120
Do you?
'Cause we can keep going.

17:41.120 --> 17:42.500
I get it.
She gets it.

17:42.500 --> 17:43.620
Oh.

17:43.620 --> 17:49.210
♪♪

17:49.210 --> 17:50.750
Cooper: Hey, guys.
Come on in.

17:50.750 --> 17:52.620
Mi casa es su casa.

17:52.620 --> 17:54.080
Cooper,
this is my house.

17:54.080 --> 17:55.670
[ Scoffs ]
What's he doing here?

17:55.670 --> 17:57.120
Yeah,
what are you doing here?

17:57.120 --> 18:00.040
He came over
to apologize to Gina.

18:05.540 --> 18:08.750
Look, I understand why
you don't like me very much.

18:08.750 --> 18:10.750
I know I can be a...

18:10.750 --> 18:12.420
Um, what was
that phrase again?

18:12.420 --> 18:14.710
The worst person
on the planet.
Right.

18:14.710 --> 18:17.250
Um,
but I'm working on it.

18:17.250 --> 18:20.120
You see this bag?

18:20.120 --> 18:21.670
You shouldn't care
that it's more expensive

18:21.670 --> 18:22.830
than anything
you have ever owned

18:22.830 --> 18:24.880
or will ever own.

18:24.880 --> 18:26.580
That's not important
anymore.

18:26.580 --> 18:28.210
Wow.

18:28.210 --> 18:30.080
You don't realize it,
but that's growth.

18:30.080 --> 18:31.580
I want us all
to be able to hang out,

18:31.580 --> 18:33.380
so if that means
I need to be less awesome,

18:33.380 --> 18:34.790
then I'm willing
to do that.

18:40.210 --> 18:41.000
Will you give me
another shot?

18:42.880 --> 18:44.540
I know
it's hard to say "yes"

18:44.540 --> 18:47.000
after he just paid himself
a compliment in his apology,

18:47.000 --> 18:49.250
but we're working on that.

18:49.830 --> 18:51.420
Okay.

18:51.420 --> 18:53.080
I'll give you
another shot.

18:53.080 --> 18:54.460
[ Chuckling ]
Awesome.

18:58.880 --> 18:59.830
Dude.

18:59.830 --> 19:01.170
Dude.

19:01.170 --> 19:02.290
Dude?

19:02.290 --> 19:03.000
Dude!

19:06.620 --> 19:08.960
You say "dude" four times,
and you're friends again.

19:08.960 --> 19:10.540
Guys have it so easy.

19:10.540 --> 19:12.040
Oliver and I
are hanging out tonight.

19:12.040 --> 19:13.120
You can come with us
if you want.

19:13.120 --> 19:15.250
Really? Cool.

19:15.250 --> 19:16.420
Um, what did you guys
have planned?

19:16.420 --> 19:18.540
I say we go bowling.

19:18.540 --> 19:19.880
We're never gonna find
an open lane.

19:19.880 --> 19:20.960
It's league night.

19:20.960 --> 19:22.580
I can get us a lane.

19:22.580 --> 19:24.170
♪♪

19:24.170 --> 19:26.170
-Yeah!
-Wow!

19:26.170 --> 19:28.040
Having a bowling alley
in your house

19:28.040 --> 19:30.040
is the stupidest thing
I've ever seen,

19:30.040 --> 19:31.880
but those appetizers
covered in shaved truffles

19:31.880 --> 19:33.000
were delicious.

19:33.000 --> 19:34.420
Yeah, it's no
pig in your living room,

19:34.420 --> 19:35.790
but I guess
it's kind of cool.

19:35.790 --> 19:37.040
[ Breathes sharply ]

19:37.040 --> 19:38.830
What happens if someone
approaches you on the street

19:38.830 --> 19:40.580
and asks for directions?

19:40.580 --> 19:43.750
Have my bodyguard
push them in the gutter?
No.

19:43.750 --> 19:46.620
You give them directions.

19:46.620 --> 19:48.080
I have so much to learn.

19:48.080 --> 19:48.880
[ Both chuckle ]

19:53.880 --> 19:55.250
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:55.250 --> 19:57.000
Great job, babe!

19:57.000 --> 19:58.120
[ Laughs ]

20:04.040 --> 20:09.460
♪♪

20:09.460 --> 20:10.920
Taylor: [ Laughs ]

20:10.920 --> 20:13.120
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:13.120 --> 20:15.120
Franklin would love this.

20:19.880 --> 20:22.380
My breakup with Franklin
was really nasty.

20:22.380 --> 20:26.170
Lots of tears,
lots of yelling.

20:26.170 --> 20:29.380
Franklin is
a pretty passionate guy.

20:29.380 --> 20:32.080
It's the quality
I like most about him,

20:32.080 --> 20:34.540
but it's also
why we broke up.

20:34.540 --> 20:35.790
Funny.

20:35.790 --> 20:38.420
I'm so sorry to hear that,
Anna-Kat.

20:38.420 --> 20:39.460
Piece of advice --

20:39.460 --> 20:41.250
don't make
the same mistake I did.

20:41.250 --> 20:44.080
Enjoy these moments.

20:44.080 --> 20:45.670
Breakups are hard,
Anna-Kat,

20:45.670 --> 20:48.420
but most relationships
aren't meant to last.

20:48.420 --> 20:50.960
But don't worry --
the good ones do.

20:50.960 --> 20:52.170
[ Doorbell rings ]

20:56.250 --> 20:57.460
♪♪

20:57.460 --> 20:58.790
Franklin, you came back!

20:58.790 --> 21:01.420
[ Dramatic music plays ]

21:01.420 --> 21:02.460
I forgot my jacket.

21:04.920 --> 21:06.540
He can't stay away
from me.

21:06.540 --> 21:10.380
♪♪
